Reference

Extract Data from Spreadsheets

These are functions for manipulating data in spreadsheets, e.g. Excel-formatted files or CSVs. Such spreadsheets often have multiple or nested headers; “merged” cells; and multiple tables in the same file or sheet.

split_cells()

Split multiple tables in spreadsheets into separate dataframes

as_header()

Create identifier columns in spreadsheet data

carry_down()

Carry spreadsheet values down column-wise

carry_right()

Carry spreadsheet values right row-wise

all_na()

Identify all-NA rows or columns in spreadsheet

row_contains() col_contains()

Identify spreadsheet rows that contain a pattern

spreadsheet_example()

Retrieve paths to packaged Excel spreadsheets

Exploration

These are functions for interactively exploring datasets.

col_values() su()

Inspect variables' unique values

search_all()

Search across all character columns

String Wrangling

These are functions for working with string values.

`%-%` `%r%`

Remove pattern matches

`%=%`

Detect pattern matches

`%e%`

Extract pattern matches

move()

Move a pattern match between columns

normalize_whitespace()

Normalize whitespace in character columns

paste_omit_na()

Concatenate strings omitting NAs
